The paper discusses a software metric and its application to both source and binary code, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE). The use of path homology as a more powerful analogue of cyclomatic complexity suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and algorithms and data structures (cs.AR, cs.DS). The experimental demonstration of path homology giving identical results to cyclomatic complexity suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and empirical methods.
